name: modpack-alpha-test
summary: "Sodu" is a mashup of "society" and "industry". A Modpack inspired by YouTuber Joyful's "social progression" server idea, to turn Minecraft's progression into a  longer, cooperation-minded experience that more closely resembles how humans work together to fulfill one another's needs. This modpack aims to do something similar while expanding the kinds of development one can achieve, ranging from a longer early game- requiring flint tools to chop trees- to creating machines with Create and Valkyrien Skies, all within survival. This is a very early pre-release and is missing some intended features and changes, such as more in-depth toolsmithing and beds not setting spawn points.
